Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Halve, peel and chop the shallot into small pieces. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Boil your #kettle{}, then pour @water for the stock{450%ml}(boiled) into a #measuring jug{} with the @vegetable stock paste{20%g}. Stir well and set aside - this is your veg stock.

Heat a drizzle of oil in an #ovenproof pan{} on medium-high heat.

> TIP: If you don't have an ovenproof pan, use a normal pan and transfer to an ovenproof dish before baking.

Once hot, add the @British smoked bacon lardons{90%g} and fry until golden, ~{4-5%mins}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. Cook bacon thoroughly.

Stir in the shallot and cook until softened, ~{3-4%mins}. Stir in the garlic and @tomato puree{30%g} and cook for ~{1%min} more.

Add the @risotto rice{175%g}, then stir and cook until the edges of the rice are translucent, ~{1-2%mins}.

Pour your veg stock into the rice and stir well to combine.

Pop a lid on the pan (or cover with #foil{}) and bake on the middle shelf of your oven until the rice is cooked and the stock has been absorbed, ~{20-25%mins}.

Meanwhile, grate the @mature cheddar cheese{40%g}.

While the risotto bakes, halve the @lemon{1/2} and squeeze the juice into a large #bowl{}.

Add the @sugar{1} and @olive oil{1} for the dressing and mix together. Set aside.

When the risotto is ready, remove it from the oven and mix in the @sun-dried tomato paste{25%g}, @peas{120%g}, Cheddar, @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g} and a knob of butter (if you have any).

Season to taste with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{} if needed.

> TIP: Add a splash of water to loosen the risotto if needed.

Add the @pea shoots{40%g} to the bowl of dressing and toss to coat.

Share the tomato and bacon risotto between your plates or bowls and serve with the salad alongside. Enjoy!